			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				FACTION- FP MILITIA, QEYNOS, KNIGHTS OF TRUTH, CORRUPT QEYNOS GUARDS, HIGHPASS GUARDS<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
1. Freeport Militia, Corrupt Qeynos Guards<BR>
  OK PEOPLE, I will tell you the best way to improve faction with the Freeport Militia, AND NOT TAKING ANY FACTIONS HITS!  First, go to High Pass Hold.  There are orcs at the entrance coming in from Kithicor Forest, they drop orc scalps.  You can loot these, and also buy them from the people camping this spawn.  After you have collected alot, go see Captain Ashlan on the bridge.  Turn them into him, and you will gain faction with the Freeport Militia, Corrupt Qeynos Guards, High Pass Guards, and a couple others.  NO FACTION HITS!! <BR>
  The other way to improve faction with the Freeport Militia without taking any hits is to loot left goblin ears in Highhold Keep.  Find the bank, then hang a left, and go down to the basement.  Goblins are there, ranging in level from 22-35.  Kill goblins, loot ears.  People will also sell them to you.  Turn them into Captain Bozec, at the top of the stairs.  This will improve faction with the same exact people as the orc scalp quest... taking NO HITS!!!<BR>
  Or kill Knights of Truth.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
2. KNIGHTS OF TRUTH<BR>
  If you don't care about your faction standing with Opal Darkbriar or Dismal Rage, here is a way to improves faction with the Knights of Truth.  Locate the Hall of Truth in North Freeport.  To the left just before you hit the bridge to the Hall of Truth, there are pirahnas.  Jump in the water and kill them.  Loot the fresh pirahna.  On top of the roof on the Hall of Truth, hail around, somebody will give you a bag to put them in.  Once the bag is filled with four fresh pirahna, hand it in.<BR>
  Or you can do what most people do, and kill orcs.<BR>
  If you don't care about your faction with the Freeport Militia, keep a look out for people killing guards in West Freeport.  They will usually let you loot the damaged militia helms, which drop of the guards, and are no-drop.  Turn these into Theron something on top of the Hall of Truth.  (hail around, i'm don't remember exactly)<BR>
  Or you can kick a guard being pulled to the tunnel in the east commons, this won't taunt them bad enough, when he dies, you get faction.<BR>
<BR>
3. QEYNOS GUARDS<BR>
  Quite simple to improve faction.  You can kill Karana bandits, or gnolls in Blackburrow.  Alot.  There are other easy ways to improve faction.  Wandering around in the docks side of Qeynos, there are two guards.  One wants muffins, the other water.  Give one muffins, and the other water.  This will hurt Corrupt Qeynos Guards faction, though.<BR>
<BR>
Matthius Ironarms<BR>
26th Season Dwarven Paladin<BR>
Druzzil Ro
				</font>
